We are \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/6500gearcats/Reefscape2025/blob/AprilTagAlignmentUsingPoseEstimator-P/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/GCPoseEstimator.java\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003ecurrently attempting\u003c/a\u003e to get accurate vision-based odometry measurements using just one limelight and are using a pretty \u003ca href=\"https://github.com/6500gearcats/Reefscape2025/blob/AprilTagAlignmentUsingPoseEstimator-P/src/main/java/frc/robot/commands/dpadAlign.java\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003eunorthodox command\u003c/a\u003e to use our estimated position to align with the reef/source. Instead of using camera inputs of AprilTags I decided to use the field layout provided by wpilib to loop through each of the april tags and get their positions, the closest Pose2d to the robot’s pose2d (constantly being updated by vision) would be the target april tag. I can then use Pathplanner’s pathFindToPosition method call to move into an offset of the reef/source based on what button is pressed. In Photonvision’s simulation this code works perfectly every time assuming you’re already very close to the april tag you want to line-up with (Note: We are using limelights but use the photonvision simulator for testing- the rationale being the limelights should provide us accurate and up-to-date pose values).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eMore real-life field practice is needed but so far it’s iffy on whether or not it works. Is this approach one that’s feasible or are there other limitations I’m not considering?\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eOur current theory is that our pose estimator is not all-as-accurate as we thought- I linked the code earlier. And for one, we have to mount the \u003cspan class=\"abbreviation\"\u003eLL\u003ctemplate class=\"tooltiptext\" data-text=\"Limelight, an integrated vision coprocessor\"\u003e\u003c/template\u003e\u003c/span\u003e on the front of the robot so when it aligns with the reef it loses sight of an april tag and resorts to odometry which is pretty inaccurate. I’m beginning to wonder if we should cut our losses and do what most teams seem to be doing which is getting the april tag data from the cameras themselves to line-up
